                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1240">Febronia of Nisibis was a martyr and nun who
          lived in a convent near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/142">Nisibis</placeName>.
          She was renown for her beauty, learning, asceticism, and bravery. She was martyred for
          refusing to marry a pagan statesman. She is venerated in the Syriac, Latin, and Greek
          traditions.</note>
